# Cloudflare Pages — SPA fallback
#
# Serve index.html (HTTP 200, no redirect) for any path that is NOT a real
# static file, so client-side routes such as /proof, /catalog, /spot-fraud,
# /asset/:id keep working on direct load and on hard refresh.
#
# Real build files are served FIRST and are NOT affected by this rule:
#   /assets/*        (Vite content-hashed JS/CSS)
#   /media/*         (images)
#   /catalog.json    (public catalog)
#
# This replaces the Vercel "rewrites" rule, which Cloudflare Pages does not read.
/*    /index.html    200
